The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for finding matchings in graphs, which are topics covered in several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), which covers combinatorial and graph-theoretic topics. The paper also involves the study of planar graphs, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the study of graph properties and their implications, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
